1:
Hear my prayer, Yahweh;
\q hear my cry to you.
\q

17:
At that time, he will respond to the prayer of the destitute;
\q he will not reject their prayer.
\q

19:
For he has looked down from the holy heights;
\q from heaven Yahweh has viewed the earth,
\q

25:
In ancient times you set the earth in place;
\q the heavens are the work of your hands.
\q

26:
They will perish, but you will remain;
\q they will all grow old like a garment;
\q like clothing, you will remove them, and they will disappear.
\q
